@startuml UseCase_Description
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FAFAFA
skinparam noteBorderColor #185FA5
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #E6F1FB
skinparam noteFontSize 12

title "Use Case Description: Menu List Page (Admin)"

note as UC01
  Use Case ID     : UC01
  Use Case Name   : View Menu List
  Actor           : Admin
  Description     : Admin views all menu items across restaurants
                    to manage or find any specific menu item.
  Preconditions   : 1. Admin is authenticated and logged in.
                    2. Admin has permission to access the Menu page.
  Postconditions  : Menu list is displayed on screen with pagination.
  ----
  Main Flow:
    1. Admin navigates to the Menu List page.
    2. System validates the Admin authentication token.
    3. System checks Admin authorization (role/permission).
    4. System fetches menu data from the database.
    5. System displays the menu list with the following fields:
       Name, Image, Price, Category, Status, Actions.
    6. Admin can proceed to search, filter, sort, or manage items.
  ----
  Alternative Flow:
    4a. No menu data found:
        - System displays "No menu items found."
    4b. Data load fails:
        - System displays an error message.
        - Admin can click Retry to reload.
  ----
  Exception Flow:
    3a. Admin has no permission:
        - System redirects to 403 Unauthorized page.
  ----
  Business Rules  : BR01 - Display menus from all restaurants in the system.
                    BR02 - Default pagination shows 20 items per page.
                    BR03 - Default sort order is Latest Updated Date.
  Non-Functional  : Response time must be under 3 seconds.
                    System must support over 10,000 menu records.
end note

note as UC02
  Use Case ID     : UC02
  Use Case Name   : Search Menu
  Actor           : Admin
  Description     : Admin searches for menu items using a keyword.
  Preconditions   : UC01 has been completed successfully.
  Postconditions  : Filtered menu list matching keyword is displayed.
  ----
  Main Flow:
    1. Admin types a keyword into the Search input.
    2. System filters menu items matching the keyword.
    3. System updates and displays the search results.
    4. System shows total number of results found.
  ----
  Alternative Flow:
    3a. No results found:
        - System displays "No results for [keyword]."
  ----
  Search Fields   : Menu Name, Description, Category Name.
end note

note as UC03
  Use Case ID     : UC03
  Use Case Name   : Filter Menu by Category
  Actor           : Admin
  Description     : Admin filters the menu list by a specific category.
  Preconditions   : UC01 has been completed successfully.
  Postconditions  : Menu list shows only items in the selected category.
  ----
  Main Flow:
    1. Admin selects a category from the Category dropdown.
    2. System applies the category filter.
    3. System displays only menus in that category.
  ----
  Alternative Flow:
    3a. No items in selected category:
        - System displays "No items found in this category."
end note

note as UC04
  Use Case ID     : UC04
  Use Case Name   : Filter Menu by Status
  Actor           : Admin
  Description     : Admin filters the menu list by status (Active / Inactive).
  Preconditions   : UC01 has been completed successfully.
  Postconditions  : Menu list shows only items with the selected status.
  ----
  Main Flow:
    1. Admin selects a status from the Status dropdown.
    2. System applies the status filter.
    3. System displays filtered results.
end note

note as UC07
  Use Case ID     : UC07
  Use Case Name   : Edit Menu
  Actor           : Admin
  Description     : Admin edits an existing menu item's information.
  Preconditions   : Admin can see the menu list from UC01.
  Postconditions  : Menu item is updated and reflected in the list.
  ----
  Main Flow:
    1. Admin clicks the Edit button on a menu item.
    2. System opens the Edit Menu form pre-filled with existing data.
    3. Admin modifies the desired fields.
    4. Admin clicks Save.
    5. System validates the input data.
    6. System saves the changes and updates the table.
    7. System shows a success notification.
  ----
  Alternative Flow:
    5a. Validation fails:
        - System shows error messages below the invalid fields.
    6a. Save fails (server error):
        - System shows an error toast notification.
  ----
  Business Rules  : BR04 - Menu name must be unique within the restaurant.
                    BR05 - Price must be a positive number.
end note

note as UC08
  Use Case ID     : UC08
  Use Case Name   : Delete Menu
  Actor           : Admin
  Description     : Admin permanently removes a menu item from the system.
  Preconditions   : Admin can see the menu list from UC01.
  Postconditions  : Menu item is removed and no longer shown in the list.
  ----
  Main Flow:
    1. Admin clicks the Delete button on a menu item.
    2. System shows a Confirm Delete dialog.
    3. Admin confirms the deletion.
    4. System deletes the menu item from the database.
    5. System removes the item from the table.
    6. System shows a success notification.
  ----
  Alternative Flow:
    3a. Admin cancels:
        - Dialog closes, no changes are made.
  ----
  Business Rules  : BR06 - Deleted menus cannot be recovered.
end note

note as UC09
  Use Case ID     : UC09
  Use Case Name   : Add New Menu
  Actor           : Admin
  Description     : Admin creates a new menu item in the system.
  Preconditions   : Admin has "Create Menu" permission.
  Postconditions  : New menu item is saved and shown in the list.
  ----
  Main Flow:
    1. Admin clicks the Add New Menu button.
    2. System opens the Add Menu form (empty).
    3. Admin fills in all required fields:
       Name, Price, Category, Image, Status.
    4. Admin clicks Submit.
    5. System validates the input.
    6. System saves the new menu item.
    7. System adds the item to the top of the list.
    8. System shows a success notification.
  ----
  Alternative Flow:
    5a. Validation fails:
        - System highlights invalid fields with error messages.
  ----
  Required Fields : Name, Price, Category, Status.
end note

@enduml